      "text": "Yes, **Jobright** (Jobright.ai) is an AI-powered job search and career acceleration platform designed to act as a personal \"AI job copilot\". It is built to automate and streamline the repetitive, time-consuming aspects of the job hunt—such as scrolling through countless listings, modifying resumes for individual roles, and filling out applications. \n\n### Key Features\n*   **AI Job Matching \u0026 Scoring:** Users can upload their resume to get matched against millions of U.S.-based listings. The tool provides a personalized \"Match Score\" for each job, indicating how well their experience aligns with the role\u0027s requirements.\n*   **Orion (AI Career Assistant):** The platform features an AI conversational agent named Orion. Users can ask Orion questions about specific roles, company culture, or how to address gaps in their qualifications for a certain position.\n*   **Resume Tailoring \u0026 Cover Letter Generation:** Jobright uses AI to instantly rewrite resumes and generate tailored cover letters specific to a target job description to help candidates pass Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS).\n*   **One-Click Auto-Apply:** Through a Google Chrome extension, the tool automates the process of filling out application forms on various job portals, significantly reducing manual data entry.\n*   **Interview Prep \u0026 Negotiation:** The platform includes an \"Interview Copilot\" that provides practice questions, voice-based interview simulation, and strategies to negotiate compensation once an offer is received.\n\n### Founders and Background\nThe platform was co-founded by **Eric Cheng (CEO)**, a Carnegie Mellon alumnus and former early engineer at Box, alongside **Ethan Zheng (CTO)**, an AI specialist with a Ph.D. from the University of Hong Kong. The idea grew from Cheng\u0027s travels across several U.S. cities, where he realized that many skilled professionals struggled to find work not due to a lack of talent, but because of information asymmetry and a lack of access to career resources. \n\nThe company is notable for scaling very rapidly with a highly lean team, raising several million dollars in venture funding, and growing its user base to over 2 million job seekers. \n\n### Pricing and Availability\nWhile Jobright offers some basic features for free, full access to its automated application engines, resume optimization, and advanced AI tools is typically offered under a premium tier, which costs around $20 per month (when billed annually). Currently, the platform mainly focuses on indexing and applying to **U.S.-based roles**, with a strong presence in tech, data, marketing, product management, and engineering sectors.",
