CPU can sustain an effective sparse computation rate of roughly 15 to 30 GFLOPs/second (taking memory overhead into account).\n*   $$\\text{Computation Time} \\approx \\frac{60 \\text{ Billion FLOPs}}{25 \\text{ GFLOPs/sec}} \\approx \\mathbf{2.4 \\text{ seconds}}$$\n*   $$\\text{Top-100 Sorting Time} \\approx \\mathbf{1.1 \\text{ seconds}}$$\n*   *Verdict:* **Total Runtime $\\approx$ 3.5 seconds**. \n\nEven on a consumer MacBook CPU, the entire matching and ranking database for 100,000 highly detailed profiles against 1,000,000 active jobs can be computed from scratch in **under 4 seconds**, provided the code leverages the `Accelerate` framework and processes the output in memory-conscious chunks.",
